text: Oldřich Tikal (born 28 November 1938) is a Czech rower who represented Czechoslovakia. He competed at the 1960 Summer Olympics in Rome with the men's coxed four where they were eliminated in the semi-finals. ==References== Category:1938 births Category:Living people Category:Czechoslovak male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of Czechoslovakia Category:Rowers at the 1960 Summer Olympics Category:Rowers from Prague Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
